{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880030284,"sessionID":"ses_2854d6db7ffe29XaN17T01Ck5i","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab2c3c50018xR8t1RtSgOD04","messageID":"msg_d7ab2b0440015TJV8ASGWl6P2k","sessionID":"ses_2854d6db7ffe29XaN17T01Ck5i","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_47956a4762544b919637b176","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PCAP analyzer example application in the AgentCube `example` module.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-037\n10: - **Module**: `example`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Files to Add\n18: \n19: | Path | Description | Type |\n20: |------|-------------|------|\n21: | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application with SandboxRunner, ReActAgent, Planner, and Reporter | New |\n22: | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Dependencies: fastapi, uvicorn, langchain-openai, scapy | New |\n23: | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition | New |\n24: | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest | New |\n25: | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Usage documentation | New |\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Files to Modify\n30: \n31: | Path | Description | Change Type |\n32: |------|-------------|-------------|\n33: | | | |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Files to Delete\n38: \n39: | Path | Description |\n40: |------|-------------|\n41: | | |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Requirements\n46: \n47: ### AR-037-001: PCAP Analyzer Module Structure\n48: \n49: The system SHALL provide a complete `example/pcap-analyzer/` module demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: AR-037-001-A — Module directory exists\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** the workspace root at `example/`\n54: - **WHEN** the directory is inspected\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap-analyzer/` subdirectory with all required files\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: AR-037-001-B — Required files present\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n60: - **WHEN** files are listed\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### AR-037-002: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Application\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-A — Application startup with API key\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n72: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL initialize LLM client, PLANNER agent, and REPORTER agent\n74: - **AND** bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-B — Application startup without API key\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n79: - **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n80: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail with an error rather than serve requests\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-C — Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n85: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload (`pcap_file` as `UploadFile`)\n86: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-D — Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n91: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field (alternative to file upload)\n92: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ### AR-037-003: SandboxRunner Integration\n97: \n98: The system SHALL provide a `SandboxRunner` class that encapsulates AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-A — SandboxRunner initialization\n101: \n102: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed with name, namespace, router_url, workload_manager_url, and warmup_sec\n103: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n104: - **THEN** it SHALL create a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n105: - **AND** be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-B — Context manager support\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is used as a context manager\n110: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n111: - **THEN** the underlying CodeInterpreterClient SHALL be properly stopped\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-C — File upload to sandbox\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path to analyze\n116: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n117: - **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded to the remote sandbox\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-D — Command execution in sandbox\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` with an active session\n122: - **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n123: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and return execution result\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### AR-037-004: LLM Orchestration (Planner + Reporter)\n128: \n129: The system SHALL implement LLM-based orchestration for PCAP analysis.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-A — Planner agent generates analysis script\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** a PCAP file is available in the sandbox\n134: - **WHEN** the PLANNER agent receives analysis request with context about the file\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL generate a Python script using scapy to analyze the PCAP\n136: - **AND** return the script as a string\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-B — Reporter agent generates human-readable report\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** analysis results from sandbox execution\n141: - **WHEN** the REPORTER agent receives the raw results\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL generate a human-readable analysis report\n143: - **AND** return the report as a string\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-C — ReAct agent coordinates flow\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service\n148: - **WHEN** a client submits a PCAP for analysis\n149: - **THEN** the ReAct agent SHALL orchestrate: upload file → generate script → execute → generate report\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### AR-037-005: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n154: \n155: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-A — Default configuration values\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n160: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL use:\n162:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n163:   - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n164:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n165:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n166:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-B — Environment variable overrides\n169: \n170: - **GIVEN** environment variables `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` are set\n171: - **WHEN** the service starts\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided values instead of defaults\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-C — Required environment variables\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** the service starts without `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ROUTER_URL`, or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n177: - **WHEN** the application attempts to start\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL raise a configuration error indicating the missing required variables\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### AR-037-006: PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n183: \n184: The system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: AR-037-006-A — Dependency file content\n187: \n188: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n189: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n190: - **THEN** it SHALL include at minimum: `fastapi>=0.120.0`, `uvicorn`, `langchain-openai`, `scapy`, `agentcube-sdk`\n191: - **AND** all versions SHALL be pinned or have compatible version specifiers\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### AR-037-007: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n196: \n197: The system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: AR-037-007-A — Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n200: \n201: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` is built\n202: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL use a Python base image, set appropriate `PYTHONPATH`, expose port `8000`, and run the FastAPI application\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: AR-037-007-B — SDK vendoring\n206: \n207: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build context includes the agentcube SDK\n208: - **WHEN** the image is built\n209: - **THEN** it SHALL include the SDK in the image for the application to import\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### AR-037-008: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n214: \n215: The system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: AR-037-008-A — Deployment manifest structure\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n220: - **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n221: - **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with appropriate container image, port, and resource configuration\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: AR-037-008-B — Environment variable wiring\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** the deployment is applied\n226: - **WHEN** the pod starts\n227: - **THEN** it SHALL have required environment variables configured:\n228:   - `OPENAI_API_KEY` (from secret)\n229:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`\n230:   - `OPENAI_MODEL`\n231:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n232:   - `ROUTER_URL`\n233:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`\n234:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`\n235:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### AR-037-009: SDK Integration\n240: \n241: The system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter operations.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-A — SDK import\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n246: - **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n247: - **THEN** it SHALL import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-B — Context manager usage\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in `SandboxRunner`\n252: - **WHEN** the runner enters context manager\n253: - **THEN** it SHALL create a session via ControlPlaneClient and initialize data plane\n254: - **AND** when exiting context, it SHALL properly stop and delete the session\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-C — SDK exception handling\n257: \n258: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n259: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n260: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (from `agentcube.exceptions`) with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### AR-037-010: PCAP Analysis Workflow\n265: \n266: The system SHALL execute a complete PCAP analysis workflow.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-A — Complete analysis flow\n269: \n270: - **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service with all required configuration\n271: - **WHEN** a client uploads a valid PCAP file to `/analyze`\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n273:   1. Upload the PCAP file to the sandbox\n274:   2. Generate analysis Python script via PLANNER\n275:   3. Execute the script in the sandbox\n276:   4. Collect execution results\n277:   5. Generate human-readable report via REPORTER\n278:   6. Return response with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-B — Invalid PCAP file handling\n281: \n282: - **GIVEN** a client uploads a file that is not a valid PCAP\n283: - **WHEN** the analysis is attempted\n284: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating the file is not a valid PCAP\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-C — Large file handling\n287: \n288: - **GIVEN** a client uploads a PCAP file exceeding reasonable size limits\n289: - **WHEN** the upload is attempted\n290: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating file size limit exceeded\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## Acceptance Criteria\n295: \n296: - [ ] AC001: `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory contains all required files\n297: - [ ] AC002: FastAPI application starts successfully with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n298: - [ ] AC003: FastAPI application fails to start without `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n299: - [ ] AC004: `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload and returns AnalyzeResponse\n300: - [ ] AC005: `/analyze` endpoint accepts path parameter as alternative\n301: - [ ] AC006: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, run, and stop methods\n302: - [ ] AC007: SandboxRunner supports context manager protocol\n303: - [ ] AC008: PLANNER agent generates Python script using scapy\n304: - [ ] AC009: REPORTER agent generates human-readable report\n305: - [ ] AC010: ReAct agent orchestrates the complete analysis flow\n306: - [ ] AC011: Configuration uses defaults when env vars are not set\n307: - [ ] AC012: Required environment variables are validated at startup\n308: - [ ] AC013: requirements.txt contains all required dependencies\n309: - [ ] AC014: Dockerfile builds successfully and runs the application\n310: - [ ] AC015: Kubernetes deployment manifest is valid and deployable\n311: - [ ] AC016: SDK exceptions are properly handled\n312: - [ ] AC017: Invalid PCAP file returns appropriate error\n313: - [ ] AC018: README.md contains usage instructions\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## Configuration Changes\n318: \n319: | Key | Old Value | New Value | Description |\n320: |-----|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n321: | | | | |\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Database Schema Changes\n326: \n327: | Table | Change | SQL |\n328: |-------|--------|-----|\n329: | | | |\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## API Changes\n334: \n335: ### New APIs\n336: \n337: | Method | Path | Description |\n338: |--------|------|-------------|\n339: | POST | `/analyze` | Analyze PCAP file with LLM orchestration |\n340: \n341: ### Modified APIs\n342: \n343: | Method | Path | Description |\n344: |--------|------|-------------|\n345: | | | |\n346: \n347: ### Deprecated APIs\n348: \n349: | Method | Path | Description |\n350: |--------|------|-------------|\n351: | | | |\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ## Architecture Notes\n356: \n357: ### Key Components\n358: \n359: | Component | Path | Description |\n360: |------|------|-------------|\n361: | Main Application | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application entry point |\n362: | SandboxRunner | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient wrapper |\n363: | Planner Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating analysis scripts |\n364: | Reporter Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating reports |\n365: | Dependencies | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Python package dependencies |\n366: | Container | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition |\n367: | Deployment | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest |\n368: \n369: ### Environment Variables\n370: \n371: | Variable | Default | Required | Description |\n372: |----------|---------|----------|-------------|\n373: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | Yes | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n374: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | No | API endpoint |\n375: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | No | Model name |\n376: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n377: | `ROUTER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Router URL |\n378: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | No | Code interpreter name |\n379: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | No | Kubernetes namespace |\n380: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | No | Sandbox warmup duration |\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## References\n385: \n386: - Proposal: `changes/AR-037/proposal.md`\n387: - SDK design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n388: - SDK spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n389: - Reference source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n(End of file - total 389 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PCAP analyzer example application in the AgentCube `example` module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-037\n- **Module**: `example`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Add\n\n| Path | Description | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880030255,"end":1775880030281}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880030288,"sessionID":"ses_2854d6db7ffe29XaN17T01Ck5i","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab2beff001JYjjlYrCQqu1ET","messageID":"msg_d7ab2b0440015TJV8ASGWl6P2k","sessionID":"ses_2854d6db7ffe29XaN17T01Ck5i","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_43507d94e0a14055bd07c090","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: 实现一个基于 AgentCube Code Interpreter 的 PCAP（Packet Capture）网络流量分析示例应用。该应用展示如何使用 Python SDK 创建代码解释器会话、执行 Python 脚本进行网络包分析，并通过 LLM 编排生成可读的分析报告。\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: ### Background\n12: \n13: AgentCube Python SDK 提供了强大的 Code Interpreter 能力，允许用户在隔离的沙箱环境中执行代码和分析文件。当前缺乏一个完整的示例应用来展示如何在真实场景中使用这些能力。\n14: \n15: PCAP 分析是一个典型的数据处理场景，需要：\n16: 1. 上传二进制网络抓包文件\n17: 2. 在隔离环境中执行 Python 脚本（使用 scapy/pyshark）\n18: 3. 解析和提取网络流量信息\n19: 4. 生成人类可读的分析报告\n20: \n21: ### Goal\n22: \n23: 1. 创建 `example/pcap-analyzer/` 模块，展示 AgentCube SDK 的完整使用方式\n24: 2. 实现基于 FastAPI 的 Web 服务，接受 PCAP 文件上传并返回分析结果\n25: 3. 集成 LLM 编排能力（Planner + Reporter 模式）\n26: 4. 提供 Dockerfile 和 K8s 部署配置\n27: 5. 编写完整的使用文档\n28: \n29: ### Value\n30: \n31: - 展示 AgentCube SDK 的最佳实践\n32: - 提供可运行的示例应用作为用户入门指南\n33: - 验证 Code Interpreter 在文件处理场景下的能力\n34: - 为未来扩展其他分析场景（如日志分析、CSV 分析）提供参考架构\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## Scope\n39: \n40: ### In-Scope\n41: \n42: - `example/pcap-analyzer/` 目录结构设计和实现\n43: - FastAPI 应用开发（文件上传、分析 endpoint）\n44: - AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient 集成\n45: - LLM 编排模块（Planner、Reporter）\n46: - Dockerfile 容器化配置\n47: - K8s deployment.yaml 部署清单\n48: - requirements.txt 依赖声明\n49: - README.md 使用文档\n50: \n51: ### Out-of-Scope\n52: \n53: - 生产级监控和告警\n54: - 认证和授权机制\n55: - PCAP 分析算法的深度优化\n56: - 其他文件格式支持（如 pcapng）\n57: - 多 PCAP 文件批量分析\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Technical Details\n62: \n63: ### Module\n64: \n65: example\n66: \n67: ### Language\n68: \n69: Python\n70: \n71: ### Size\n72: \n73: M\n74: \n75: ### Key Components\n76: \n77: | 组件 | 文件 | 说明 |\n78: |------|------|------|\n79: | 主应用 | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI 应用，包含 SandboxRunner、ReActAgent、Planner、Reporter |\n80: | 依赖 | `requirements.txt` | fastapi, uvicorn, langchain-openai, scapy |\n81: | 容器化 | `Dockerfile` | Python 3.10 基础镜像 |\n82: | 部署 | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + Service |\n83: | 文档 | `README.md` | 使用说明 |\n84: \n85: ### Architecture\n86: \n87: ```\n88: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n89: │   Client    │────▶│  FastAPI App     │────▶│ AgentCube SDK   │\n90: │  (Upload)   │     │  (Planner/       │     │ (CodeInterpreter│\n91: └─────────────┘     │   Reporter)      │     │  Client)        │\n92:                     └──────────────────┘     └────────┬────────┘\n93:                                                      │\n94:                                                      ▼\n95:                                             ┌────────────────┐\n96:                                             │  Code Interp.  │\n97:                                             │  Sandbox       │\n98:                                             │  (scapy anal.) │\n99:                                             └────────────────┘\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### Configuration\n103: \n104: | 环境变量 | 默认值 | 说明 |\n105: |----------|--------|------|\n106: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | LLM API 密钥（必需） |\n107: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | LLM API 端点 |\n108: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | LLM 模型 |\n109: | `ROUTER_URL` | - | AgentCube Router URL（必需） |\n110: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | - | Workload Manager URL（必需） |\n111: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | 会话名称 |\n112: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | K8s 命名空间 |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## Implementation Plan\n117: \n118: ### Phase 1: 核心应用开发\n119: \n120: 1. 完善 `pcap_analyzer.py` 主应用\n121: 2. 实现 SandboxRunner 类封装 CodeInterpreterClient\n122: 3. 实现 LLM 编排模块（Planner、Reporter）\n123: \n124: ### Phase 2: 部署配置\n125: \n126: 1. 优化 Dockerfile\n127: 2. 完善 deployment.yaml\n128: 3. 配置环境变量和资源配置\n129: \n130: ### Phase 3: 测试和文档\n131: \n132: 1. 本地运行测试\n133: 2. 编写 README.md 使用文档\n134: 3. 验证端到端分析流程\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## Impact Analysis\n139: \n140: ### Positive Impact\n141: \n142: - 为 AgentCube 提供可运行的示例应用\n143: - 降低用户学习门槛\n144: - 验证 SDK 在文件处理场景的能力\n145: - 可复用于其他类似分析场景\n146: \n147: ### Risks\n148: \n149: | 风险 | 影响 | 缓解措施 |\n150: |------|------|----------|\n151: | LLM API 不可用 | 分析流程中断 | 添加错误处理和降级提示 |\n152: | 网络超时 | 请求失败 | 配置合理的超时时间 |\n153: | PCAP 文件过大 | 内存溢出 | 添加文件大小限制 |\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## Alternatives Considered\n158: \n159: ### Alternative 1: CLI 工具方式\n160: \n161: 仅提供命令行接口，无需 Web 服务。\n162: \n163: **原因未采用**：CLI 方式无法充分展示 AgentCube 的 Web 集成能力，且不易于用户测试。\n164: \n165: ### Alternative 2: 使用现有 Dify 插件\n166: \n167: 复用 AR-036 的 Dify 插件能力。\n168: \n169: **原因未采用**：Dify 插件面向 Dify 平台用户，此示例面向直接使用 SDK 的开发者，场景不同。\n170: \n171: ### Alternative 3: 纯脚本方式\n172: \n173: 不提供 Web 接口，仅提供分析脚本。\n174: \n175: **原因未采用**：缺少用户交互界面，不便于演示和测试。\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## Dependencies\n180: \n181: - **agentcube-sdk** — AgentCube Python SDK\n182: - **fastapi** ==0.120.0 — Web 框架\n183: - **uvicorn** — ASGI 服务器\n184: - **langchain-openai** — LLM 集成\n185: - **scapy** — PCAP 解析库\n186: - **pydantic** — 数据验证\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Timeline\n191: \n192: | 阶段 | 预计工作量 | 里程碑 |\n193: |------|-----------|--------|\n194: | Phase 1 | 2d | 核心应用完成 |\n195: | Phase 2 | 1d | 部署配置完成 |\n196: | Phase 3 | 1d | 测试和文档完成 |\n197: \n198: **总计**: 约 4 人日\n\n(End of file - total 198 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n## Summary\n\n实现一个基于 AgentCube Code Interpreter 的 PCAP（Packet Capture）网络流量分析示例应用。该应用展示如何使用 Python SDK 创建代码解释器会话、执行 Python 脚本进行网络包分析，并通过 LLM 编排生成可读的分析报告。\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube Python SDK 提供了强大的 Code Interpreter 能力，允许用户在隔离的沙箱环境中执行代码和分析文件。当前缺乏一个完整的示例应用来展示如何在真实场景中使用这些能力。\n\nPCAP 分析是一个典型的数据处理场景，需要：\n1. 上传二进制网络抓包文件\n2. 在隔离环境中执行 Python 脚本（使用 scapy/pyshark）\n3. 解析和提取网络流量信息\n4. 生成人类可读的分析报告\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880030252,"end":1775880030285}}}}
